Malaysia Stock Movers: AirAsia, Esso Malaysia, MMC

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a   a n d   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-06-03T01:57:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-03/malaysia-stock-movers-airasia-esso-malaysia-mmc.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:33 a.m. in Kuala Lumpur.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index rose 3.59 points, or 0.2
percent, to 1,561.63. The measure is set for a 0.8 percent gain
this week, advancing for a fourth week.        AirAsia Bhd. (AIRA)  ,  Southeast Asia ’s largest discount
airline, climbed 1 percent to 3.02 ringgit. Tune Air Sdn., the
biggest shareholder in AirAsia, sold 55.5 million shares, or a 2
percent stake in the budget airline, according to a stock
exchange filing. The sales trimmed Tune Air’s stake to 23.1
percent, it said.        Esso Malaysia Bhd. (ESSO)  , a petroleum products
retailer, gained 1.6 percent to 5.18 ringgit. Esso proposed a
300 million-ringgit ($100 million), seven-year Islamic bonds
program, the company said in a statement.  MMC Corp. (MMC MK), a Malaysian power producer and ports
operator, increased 1.5 percent to 2.79 ringgit. The company was
upgraded to “trading buy” from “neutral” at OSK Research
Sdn. on speculation that its 51 percent-owned Malakoff Corp. may
have won rights to expand its Tanjung Bin power plant in Johor.  To contact the reporter on this story:
